						<div class="postbody">I took a video capture of the ROM running in my real NES, and the capture is surprisingly faithful to what I saw on my TV screen :<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://youtu.be/l-y9gaU-pR4">https://youtu.be/l-y9gaU-pR4</a><!-- m --><br /><br />When you watch this in 60fps, you can see some that combinations of colors cause the upper left square to visibly flicker, which I thought weird.  I would have lingered longer, but I couldn't see it on the capture device's viewer, so I thought the effect was lost.  When I converted the video to 60fps, it reappeared.</div>

					
